(meaning system-design "Horizontal scaling: stateless services + load balancer. Session state in Redis, not in-process.") <0.90, 0.85>
(meaning system-design "Caching: Cache-aside (app checks cache, miss = fetch DB + populate). Write-through (write to cache + DB). CDN for static.") <0.90, 0.85>
(meaning system-design "DB selection: Postgres (ACID, JSON, complex queries) | MongoDB (flexible schema, horizontal) | Cassandra (high write, time-series) | Redis (cache/sessions/leaderboards) | Elasticsearch (full-text sear") <0.90, 0.85>
(meaning system-design "Indexing: B-tree (range queries) | Hash (equality only) | GIN (JSONB/full-text) | Partial index (WHERE clause). Always EXPLAIN ANALYZE.") <0.90, 0.85>
(meaning system-design "Kafka: High-throughput durable log. Partitions for parallelism. Consumer groups for competing consumers. At-least-once delivery. Idempotent consumers required.") <0.90, 0.85>
(meaning system-design "Microservices: Only when team size justifies (Conway's Law). Circuit breaker. Service mesh (Istio). Saga pattern for distributed transactions.") <0.90, 0.85>
(meaning architecture "SOLID: Single Responsibility | Open/Closed | Liskov Substitution | Interface Segregation | Dependency Inversion") <0.90, 0.85>
(meaning architecture "Clean Architecture: Entities → Use Cases → Interface Adapters → Frameworks. Dependencies point inward.") <0.90, 0.85>
(meaning architecture "Design patterns: Factory (creation) | Observer (events) | Strategy (interchangeable algorithms) | Decorator (extend behaviour) | Repository (data access)") <0.90, 0.85>
(meaning architecture "Event sourcing: Immutable append-only log. State = replaying events. CQRS natural companion.") <0.90, 0.85>
(meaning architecture "CQRS: Separate read model from write model. Scale independently.") <0.90, 0.85>
(meaning languages "Python: GIL prevents true thread parallelism for CPU-bound. Use multiprocessing. asyncio for I/O. Generators = lazy. Decorators = @functools.wraps.") <0.90, 0.85>
(meaning languages "TypeScript: Structural typing. Mapped types. Conditional types T extends U ? X : Y. Discriminated unions for type narrowing.") <0.90, 0.85>
(meaning languages "Rust: One owner. Borrowing: &T immutable (multiple ok), &mut T mutable (only one). Lifetimes prevent dangling refs. Result<T,E> for errors.") <0.90, 0.85>
(meaning languages "Go: Goroutines (~2KB stack). Channels (buffered vs unbuffered). Context for cancellation. Duck typing interfaces.") <0.90, 0.85>
